snippet.textDisplay: A problem that I am noticing is that a lot of the people who loved The Last Jedi were pretty silent in comparison to the mounds of videos on YouTube and social media from people who hated The Last Jedi. There were even protests and campaigns to retcon The Last Jedi. The people who hated that movie were impossible to ignore and, at least on the internet, they were the dominant voice. Now that we have The Rise of Skywalker, it would be strange to not address some of the backlash (although JJ Abrams might have taken that a bit far in this movie). But now, people who loved The Last Jedi are very vocal about how they feel this movie disrespected Rian Johnson and the elements developed in his film. Maybe it is the YouTube algorithm, but it also seems that people who hated the Last Jedi are silent about their love for The Rise of Skywalker. I think overall, Star Wars has become so large that it is impossible to satisfy all of its fans but i think moving forward, the only way Disney can find success is if it does what it is doing with The Mandolorian, which is exploring new territory. New characters, different time periods, new points of view. You cannot compete with nostalgia and you are setting yourself up for failure when you try. In the future, I hope Disney will continue to explore new territory and will learn it's lesson about planning out films before setting directors loose to make their own vision. My advice TO ANY DISGRUNTLED FANS: take a break. I bet you if you took a break from the saga films for a year or two and then came back to them, you would like them a lot more. I know that has already happened for many people who hated the prequels.

snippet.textDisplay:
JJ's entire shtick is cheap nostalgia references and his stupid mystery boxes. He couldn't come up with something new and interesting to save his life. I knew from the start as soon as he was announced as the director of TFA that this trilogy would suck. If he had been forced to stick to it for all three movies, it might have been tolerable. But no, he had to drop out and tap RJ to do TLJ, which was also a bad move, obviously. Then when the fandom breaks over TLJ, they beg JJ to come back to fix it, which was, arguably, the worst possible choice since he couldn't possibly do anything other than double down on his stupid crap.

JJ: "Oh, look. It's the remains of the second death star! And there's Lando! Isn't that cool? Oh, and I wonder what's in this mystery b.. I mean holocron! OMG! The Emperor is back!"
Me: 🤮🤮


I laughed when fans were talking about how relieved they were that JJ was coming back to fix things. I was like, "You seriously don't understand anything. It's only going to get worse."
Honestly, I think even someone like Michael Bay would have done a better job than JJ at coming up with some way to finish out the trilogy. He at least occasionally has some interesting and creative story ideas.

Satisfying the fans is not impossible! Baby Yoda. Mic Drop. This is the Jar Jar principle done right. Something cute and cuddly and funny stuck in the middle of the dirty nasty post-war outer systems.

Yes it's cheap move, but we all know it's not just Baby Yoda either. Favreau and Filoni are actually immersing people in the Galaxy Far Far Away, not trying to make a generic popcorn flick with a brand slapped on-top.
Mandalorian is far from having the highest production values of the Star Wars franchise and it shows that the fans are NOT hard to satisfy, Disney just screwed up their trilogy in ways that no one could have imagined.

snippet.textDisplay:
7:40 - Dan - THis movie shows that there was no plan for the trilogy.

Uhhh . . . this was revealed when TLJ came out. With the major disconnects between TFA and TLJ, Kathleen, JJ, Rian, everyone admitted, that there was no trilogy arc. They were playing it by ear and taking it 1 movie at a time with director/writer teams having basically free reign. This is why people were so upset with TLJ, because the "subverting your expectations" was such BS . . . it was for the sake of some grand story. It was literally for Rian going "I can do whatever I want and I want to mess with people".


Also, all the disconnect discussion Dan talks about between TLJ and RoS . . while it is definitely more pronounced, there is that same disconnect between TFA and TLJ . . . yet its ok for the middle movie to do but its a major sin for the last movie to do . . . I love you guys but come on.
